      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MACHX THE STRANGER (1) did a good job to finish fourth last start at Menangle. Came from much wider than this for second at Wagga prior. Likely to get the favours from the inside draw and has the talent to take this out. KEAYANG KAUNA (4) drew wide and worked last start so prepared to overlook that result. Had recorded a string of top-two finishes prior so deserves another chance. SNEAK A PEEK NZ (8) was successful from this same barrier at the latest appearance, scoring by 3.2 metres at Leeton. May need luck at some stage but if it comes her way she can make it two on the trot. BOLZANO NZ (9) draws on the second line this time but goes well at this distance and comes right into contention after scoring last start by a neck at Redcliffe.",
